com.novartis.opensource.yada

Class YADAQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.novartis.opensource.yada.YADAQuery

  • public class YADAQuery
extends Object
    The processing unit for a YADA query, containing the following, where applicable:
    • Stored code
    • Parsed code
    • List of YADAParams
    • Lists of PreparedStatements for query and result count
    • List of CallableStatements
    • List of URLs
    • List of cookie names, for REST queries, where specified
    • Array of parameterized columns
    • Array of columns referenced by SQL IN clauses
    • SQL transactional info
    • Connection
    • SOAPConnection
    • List of list of values to be processed
    • List of YADAQueryResults
    • JDBCAdaptor class and object
    Since:
    0.4.0.0
    Author:
    David Varon

      • addParamCount

        public void addParamCount(int row,
                 int paramCountToAdd)
        Stores the number of yada parameters contained in the query string. The param count can vary if a query contains a function with a dynamic argument list, such as an SQL IN clause. Consequently, param counts are indexed to the data-map list.
        Parameters:
        row - the index of the data map in the list
        paramCountToAdd - number of params for row

      • addDataTypes

        public void addDataTypes(int row,
                char[] dataTypesToAdd)
        Stores the number of yada parameter data types referenced in the query string. The data type list can vary if a query contains a function with a dynamic argument list, such as an SQL IN clause. Consequently, data types are stored in arrays, and indexed to the data-map list.
        Parameters:
        row - the index of the data map in the list
        dataTypesToAdd - array of data types

        row - the index of the data map in the list

      • addRequestParams

        public void addRequestParams(List<YADAParam> params,
                    int index)
        Stores the request-level (global) parameters in the YADAQuery object for easier downstream utilization. This method is distinct from addYADAQueryParams(List) in that it will not replace a parameter value already associated to the query even if it's overrideable
        Parameters:
        params - list of parameter objects
        index - the position of the query in the request when using JSONParams, otherwise 0
        Since:
        0.6.1.0

        Parameters:

      • addYADAQueryParams

        public void addYADAQueryParams(List<YADAParam> params)
        Stores the query-level parameters in the YADAQuery object for easier downstream utilization. Care is taken to ensure non-overrideable default parameters are not mutated, nor duplicate parameters are added.
        Parameters:
        params - list of parameter objects

      • replaceParam

        public void replaceParam(String key,
                String value)
        Replaces the value of YADAParam with name key with value, but only if the existing YADAParam is overridable. If the param doesn't exist, it is added. If the param is not overrideable, this method exits silently.
        Parameters:
        key - name of parameter for which to replace value
        value - new value for parameter
        See Also:
        replaceParam(YADAParam)

      • replaceParam

        public void replaceParam(YADAParam param)
        Replaces the value of YADAParam with values encapsulated by param, but only if the existing YADAParam is overridable. If the param doesn't exist, it is added. If the param is not overrideable, this method exits silently.
        Parameters:
        param - parameter object containing replacement values
